      "type": "eq",
      "start": 8,
      "end": 28,
      "html": "<section class=\"slide eq\"><ul class=\"eq-lines\"><li id=\"imp89sfoq1a\" class=\" eq-item eq-title \" > Start with the equation </li><li id=\"imp89sfoq1b\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ 2x + 3 = 11 $$ </li><li id=\"imp89sfoq1c\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ 2x = 8 $$ </li><li id=\"imp89sfoq1d\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ \\frac{2x}{2}=\\frac{8}{2} $$ </li><li id=\"imp89sfoq1e\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ x = 4 $$ </li><li id=\"imp89sfoq1f\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > The equation is solved. </li></ul><div class=\"eq-side-panel\"><div id=\"imp89sfoq1a-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"eq.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1a-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Keep variables on one side. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1b-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > We want to isolate x. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1b-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Remove constants first. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1b-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > 11-3 </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1b-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Subtract from both sides. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1b-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Balance must remain equal. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1b-sp-6\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Every operation affects both sides. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1c-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"box.webp\" /></div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1c-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The constant has been removed. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1d-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Now divide both sides by 2. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1d-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The coefficient disappears. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1d-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > 2x÷2=x </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1d-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Only x remains. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1d-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The equation becomes simpler. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1d-sp-6\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Always divide both sides equally. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1e-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"image.png\" /></div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1e-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The variable is isolated. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1f-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Check the answer mentally. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1f-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Substitute back if needed. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1f-sp-3\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Verification builds confidence. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1f-sp-4\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Correct structure prevents mistakes. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1f-sp-5\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Each step stayed balanced. </div><div id=\"imp89sfoq1f-sp-6\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The logic remained visible. </div></div></section>",
